  "title": "Amar-Suena 10 (RIME 3/2.01.03.10 composite)",
  "language": "sumerian",
  "translation_source": "ORACC ETCSRI — CC BY-SA 3.0",
  "source_url": "https://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/etcsri/Q000985",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q000985.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) I am Amar-Suena , whose name was proclaimed by Enlil in Nibru , the steadfast supporter of Enlil's temple , the powerful king , king of Urim , king of the four quarters ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000985.10",
      "line_range": "10",
      "translation": "(i 10) The name of this statue is \" Amar-Suena is the beloved of Urim \"."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q000985.13",
      "line_range": "13",
      "translation": "(i 13) Whoever removes this statue from the place it was set up , tears out its socle , may Nanna , king of Urim , ( and ) Ningal , the mother of Urim , curse him ! May they put an end to his lineage !"
    }
  ],
